---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Testing" description="Configure Jest to work with React Native Vector Icons">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-12 sm:px-6">

    <!-- Page Header -->
    <h1 class="gradient-text text-4xl font-bold mb-4" style="font-family: var(--font-heading)">
      Testing
    </h1>
    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-12" style="color: var(--color-text-muted)">
      Configure Jest to mock native font loading and prevent errors in your test suite.
    </p>

    <!-- Jest Configuration -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6" style="font-family: var(--font-heading); color: var(--color-text)">
        Jest Configuration
      </h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--color-text-muted)">
        When running tests with <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm" style="background-color: var(--color-surface); color: var(--color-accent-cyan); font-family: var(--font-mono)">jest</code>,
        you need to mock out the native code loading to prevent errors.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3" style="font-family: var(--font-heading); color: var(--color-accent-cyan)">
        1. Add moduleNameMapper for TTF files
      </h3>
      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--color-text-muted)">
        In your <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm" style="background-color: var(--color-surface); font-family: var(--font-mono)">jest.config.js</code>, add a module name mapper to intercept
        <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm" style="background-color: var(--color-surface); font-family: var(--font-mono)">.ttf</code> imports:
      </p>
      <div class="code-block terminal-dots mb-8">
        <pre class="px-4 pb-4 pt-2"><code>// jest.config.js
module.exports = {'{'}
  // ...other config
  moduleNameMapper: {'{'}
    '\\.(ttf)$': '&lt;rootDir&gt;/__mocks__/file-mock.js',
  {'}'},
{'}'}</code></pre>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3" style="font-family: var(--font-heading); color: var(--color-accent-cyan)">
        2. Create the file mock
      </h3>
      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--color-text-muted)">
        Create <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm" style="background-color: var(--color-surface); font-family: var(--font-mono)">__mocks__/file-mock.js</code>:
      </p>
      <div class="code-block terminal-dots mb-8">
        <pre class="px-4 pb-4 pt-2"><code>// __mocks__/file-mock.js
module.exports = {'{}'};</code></pre>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3" style="font-family: var(--font-heading); color: var(--color-accent-cyan)">
        3. Mock the common library
      </h3>
      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--color-text-muted)">
        Create <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm" style="background-color: var(--color-surface); font-family: var(--font-mono)">__mocks__/@react-native-vector-icons/common.js</code>
        to prevent native module loading errors:
      </p>
      <div class="code-block terminal-dots mb-4">
        <pre class="px-4 pb-4 pt-2"><code>// __mocks__/@react-native-vector-icons/common.js
module.exports = {'{'}
  createIconSet: () =&gt; "icon",
{'}'};</code></pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Summary -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <div class="p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4" style="background-color: var(--color-surface); border-color: var(--color-accent-cyan);">
        <p class="text-sm font-medium mb-1" style="color: var(--color-accent-cyan); font-family: var(--font-heading)">Summary</p>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-muted)">
          With these three files in place, Jest will be able to run your tests without encountering native font loading errors.
          The TTF mapper redirects font imports to an empty module, and the common library mock replaces
          <code class="text-xs px-1 py-0.5 rounded" style="background-color: var(--color-bg); font-family: var(--font-mono)">createIconSet</code>
          with a no-op.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
